tested by a bizarre crisis, a hostage-taking drama at the highest
levels of government that is exposing simmering ethnic tensions.
And the political crisis is rapidly veering toward an economic
calamity, as tourists stay away and the European Union boycotts
sugar, Fiji's dominant cash crop. By Sam Howe Verhovek.
