   WOMEN-FOREIGN-POLICY (United Nations) _ American women are more
likely than men to frame their foreign policy concerns around
global social issues like health, poverty and human rights, a new
poll has found. The survey, commissioned by the Aspen Institute,
was released to coincide with a special General Assembly session on
the progress of the world's women. By Barbara Crossette.
