<P>
   TELECOMMUNICATIONS-RATES (Washington) _ With great fanfare last
week, AT&AMP;T and the Federal Communications Commission announced that
millions of telephone customers would see lower bills as the
company passed on savings from a government-ordered reduction in
the fees that long-distance companies pay to local phone companies.
But on the day of the announcement, AT&AMP;T also filed documents with
the commission that said the company would actually be raising most
of the per-minute charges on the basic accounts of millions of
customers who make few calls, in some cases by as much as 163
percent. Exclusive. By Stephen Labaton.
