<P>
   WORKPLACE-LAWSUITS (Undated) _ Employment lawyers say there is a
new combativeness in corporate America against litigation-minded
employees. In the past, companies would usually wait until sued by
an employee. Now, apparently concluding that a good offense is the
best defense, an increasing number of employers are filing
preemptive lawsuits aimed at scaring off potential plaintiffs. By
Sana Siwolop.
