<P>
   WWII-JEWISH-CHILDREN (Paris) _ In the village of Chabannes in
the Creuse region of central France, from 1939 to 1943 some 400
Jewish children found a safehaven. The moving story of this
unlikely community has now been rescued in a documentary, ``The
Children of Chabannes.'' By Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   TINY-APARTMENTS (New York) _ In the most ingenious small
Manhattan apartments, designers and their clients become
illusionists. They make beds disappear, tables double in height and
televisions spin between two rooms at once. By Elaine Louie.
