racial disparity in prison sentencing, with figures for every
state. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS &LR;  (``p'' code)
</P>
<P>
   ALA-JUDGE (Atlanta) _ Judge Roy Moore, who fought to keep the
Ten Commandments in his courtroom, won the GOP nomination for chief
justice of the state Supreme Court with 55 percent of the vote in a
four-way race, avoiding a runoff. By Kevin Sack.
</P>
<P>
   NJ-ELECT (Trenton, N.J.) _ Folo on the New Jersey primary races.
By David M. Halbfinger.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT1.
</P>
