San Francisco _  OFF THE WALL  _ Reggie Glow leads a double life:
subtle and hardly noticeable during the day, but a real standout
when the lights go down. Reggie Glow is not anyone you'll ever
meet, however. It's a carpet made by Shaw Industries that glows in
the dark. In natural or incandescent light, it looks like a
traditional carpet. But when the lights are turned off, patterns in
the rug pop out and keep glowing for hours. 
 By Terry Nagel  
