 CHRON  
 Editors note: The San Francisco Chronicle rounds up the best
of  the unusual for home and garden in this regular feature, Off
the 
 Wall.   OFF THE WALL: Dishwashers Go in Disguise  
   
   
 By Holly Ocasio Rizzo  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
   
 SAN FRANCISCO _  A fashionable dishwasher can't wear a dishwasher's
face these days. It masquerades as a fine wooden drawer, or it's
dolled up with stainless steel, like a surgical cabinet.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Now it also can sport a waist-high magnetic art mural disguising
it as a wine cooler, a china cabinet or even a small pet.
</P>
<P>
   The chemistry behind the panels belongs to Janie Atkinson and
her son, Gregory. Janie Atkinson started a decorative painting
business in 1976 in Atlanta, specializing in faux fax  &LR; finishes,
murals and stenciling. Gregory Atkinson spent three years in the
sign-making business before branching into real estate renovation.
</P>
<P>
   Together, the Atkinsons saw a link between their talents and the
need for lovelier kitchens in hot housing markets.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kitchens are becoming more of a focal point in the home,''
Janie Atkinson says.
</P>
<P>
   Mother painted in her customary trompe l'oeil style; son
searched for the perfect screen printer and the perfect background
material, which turns out to feel like canvas, he says.
</P>
<P>
   The panels measure 231/2 inches wide by 181/2 inches high for
dishwashers, plus one cabinet design measuring 24 by 341/2 inches.
A light adhesive attaches the cabinet panel; light adhesive with
magnetic material fastens the dishwasher panels.
</P>
<P>
   What can a dishwasher look like besides itself? Like art works,
the possibilities have titles: ``Wine Cooler,'' ``Blue &AMP; White
China,'' ``Herb Garden.'' ``Children's Drawing Board'' features an
empty area on which children can write with washable crayons. For
winter, there's ``Holiday Wreath.'' For pet owners or wannabes,
``Cat &AMP; Mouse,'' ``The Aquarium'' and, for cabinets, ``The Perfect
Pet,'' depicting a dog asleep.
</P>
<P>
   Turn the dial to ``heavy wash.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
WHERE TO GET IT
</P>
<P>
   Door Decor panels _ seven for dishwashers and one for a base-end
cabinet _ are available for $69.95 plus shipping and handling by
calling (877) 884-8058 or visiting  &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; www.doordecorllc.com &LR; . Or, using the order form from the Web site,
fax (843) 763-1157 or mail to Door Decor LLC, 1023 Wappoo Road,
Suite A-11, Charleston, SC 29407.
</P>
</TEXT>
