<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BEERNUT-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FLENS ISN'T WORTH THE BOTTLE IT COMES IN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAUL BOURGEOIS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Flens is more notable for the bottle than what's in it.
</P>
<P>
   It's made by Flensburger Braueri in Flensburg, Germany, where it
proudly claims to be ``Germany's No. 1 Swing-Top Beer.''
</P>
<P>
   Now this is much like saying the Mavericks are the No. 1 NBA
team in all of North Texas. Which also reminds me of my
second-to-last ex-mother-in-law. ``The best thing I can say about
you is you are my very favorite son-in-law,'' she would tell me. Of
course, I was her only son-in-law.
</P>
<P>
   It's faint praise, but what else can you do to tout Flens when
the brew, particularly by German standards, is highly ordinary.
</P>
<P>
   Flens appears cloudy. The color is a dull burnt orange.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's probably cloudy because of fiber and minerals,'' said The
Rev, a part-time friend, full-time neighbor and self-frocked
minister.
</P>
<P>
   At a recent tasting, The Rev was more interested in rounding up
the empties than savoring the brew.
</P>
<P>
   As for me, I've never understood the need for a beer that is
easily reclosed, particularly when it comes in a puny 12-ounce
bottle, as does the Flens.
</P>
<P>
   There are a few rules in life worth remembering: Clean up your
messes; treat your neighbor nice 'cause you know how those ``quiet
types who keep to themselves'' can turn on you; and if you open a
bottle of beer, finish it.
</P>
<P>
   The Rev said he's never had the need to reclose a bottle of
beer, but he finds the bottles handy.
</P>
<P>
   Too bad that Flens isn't worth the bottles it comes in.
</P>
<P>
   It has a nice aroma of hops, but the taste is thin and
undistinguished. It has a very slight bitter aftertaste.
</P>
<P>
   The Rev and I give Flens a 1 on the 0-5 international scale. The
bottle rates a 4.
</P>
<P>
   (Paul Bourgeois is beer critic for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
