dangerously out-of-touch spendthrift. The race for the middle began
even before all the votes were counted in the New Jersey primary
Tuesday night that left Franks as the apparent Republican nominee.
And Franks' attack raised a question that could define the race _
can he succeed in turning the liberal politics and record-setting
spending that won Corzine the Democratic nomination into
liabilities big enough to keep Corzine from winning the election?
By David M. Halbfinger.
