<P>
   CONTACT-YATES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ She doesn't sing. Doesn't utter a word, in fact. Her
character doesn't even have a name. And she's the biggest thing on
Broadway. Deborah Yates, a Texas native and honors graduate of
Southern Methodist University, is the Girl in the Yellow Dress in
``Contact,'' the acclaimed ``dance-play'' that won Best Musical at
the Tony Awards on Sunday. Yates herself was nominated, a fact
she's still coming to terms with. By MARK LOWRY. Story will move in
``e'' entertainment category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Atlanta Braves made the right decision when they
shipped motormouth relief pitcher John Rocker to the minor leagues.
But why won't the team take credit for doing the right thing? By
BILL THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
