A7238 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX     06-07 0934
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE TIME IS RIPE FOR BLACKBERRY JAM CAKES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Who knew there was so much blackberry jam cake around these
parts? Our readers, that's who. We were inundated with responses to
a recent request for this old-fashioned dessert.
</P>
<P>
   Helen Scarth of Burleson, Texas, sent the first recipe. The
second was sent by Ann Barton, who credits a Texas Power and Light
publication. Carol Lippincott's version includes a boiled white
frosting.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BLACKBERRY JAM CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12-16
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 4 eggs
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon ground cloves
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon allspice
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 cups flour
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup raisins
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/2 cups blackberry jam
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan _ not a bundt pan.
</P>
<P>
   Cream butter and sugar together. Add remaining ingredients
except raisins, jam and pecans. Mix well. Stir in raisins, jam and
nuts.
</P>
<P>
   Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.
</P>
<P>
   Turn out of pan after 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   FROSTING:
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   Melt and bring to boil. Apply frosting every 10 minutes while
cake is still warm.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 637 calories, 29 grams fat, 93
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, 107 milligrams cholesterol,
315 milligrams sodium, 41 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BLACKBERRY JAM CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8-10
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup raisins
</P>
<P>
   _ 8 1/2 ounce-can crushed pineapple
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 5 eggs
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup blackberry jam
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 1/2 cups sifted flour
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon nutmeg
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 teaspoon ground cloves
</P>
<P>
   _ 2/3 cup buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Soak raisins in juice drained from pineapple several hours or
overnight. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs,
one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in jam.
</P>
<P>
   Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed
mixture with buttermilk. Drain raisins. Stir in raisins, pineapple
and pecans. Pour batter into paper-lined 9-by-13-by-2-inch pan.
</P>
<P>
   Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.
</P>
<P>
   (Personal note: My grandma always told me that when a cake
recipe called for buttermilk, to stir the baking soda into it and
not sift it into the dry ingredients. This improves the texture, in
our family's opinion.)
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 610 calories, 29 grams fat, 84
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 156 milligrams cholesterol,
325 milligrams sodium, 43 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BLACKBERRY JAM CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12-16
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 4 large eggs, room temperature
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 cups cake flour, measured after sifting
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 teaspoons baking powder
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/8 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon ground cloves
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon lemon extract
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup fairly firm blackberry jam, preferably seedless
</P>
<P>
   Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy in a large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well. If using an electric mixer,
place butter, sugar and 2 eggs in a large, deep bowl and beat 4
minutes at high speed. Add remaining 2 eggs, one at a time, and
beat well. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves
together three times. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture
alternately with milk, a small amount each time, ending with flour
mixture; beat well. Add lemon extract and rind; then add jam. Spoon
batter into three greased and floured layer pans. Bake in a
preheated 350-degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake tests
done. Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes. Great with Never Fail White
Icing. If making cake for a party, use two batches of icing _ one
for putting between the layers, the other for top and sides of
cake.
</P>
<P>
   NEVER FAIL WHITE ICING:
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 medium-size or large egg whites
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/2 cups sifted sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 5 tablespoons cold water
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/2 teaspoons light corn syrup
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   Place all ingredients with exception of vanilla in top of a
double boiler over boiling water. Beat with electric mixer at high
speed. Cut down mixture from sides of pan with spatula as it cooks.
Beat constantly about 7 minutes or until icing will stand in peaks
and has a high gloss. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
</P>
<P>
   Center a layer of cake on cake plate and put 5 heaping
tablespoons icing in a circle on top and gently spread toward the
sides. Use a dinner knife or 1-inch-wide spatula for spreading.
Position top cake layer and repeat icing method. To ice the sides,
apply a tablespoon of icing at top of side, working it down as you
go around the cake. Repeat until cake is completely covered.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 316 calories, 14 grams fat, 41
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, 113 milligrams cholesterol,
296 milligrams sodium, 40 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-07-00 1638EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
