</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With MICROSOFT and MICROSOFT-JUDGE. Moving in (w) Washington (f)
financial categories.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   THOMAS PENFIELD JACKSON
</P>
<P>
   Age: 63
</P>
<P>
   Personal: Married three times, now to Pat Jackson, a private
school official. Two grown daughters and two granddaughters.
</P>
<P>
   Education: Dartmouth College, 1958; Harvard Law School, 1964.
</P>
<P>
   Prior big cases: Sentenced then-Washington Mayor Marion Barry
Jr. to six months in jail for cocaine possession. Ordered ex-Sen.
Bob Packwood, R-Ore., to turn over damaging diaries to the Senate
Ethics Committee in its probe of sexual harassment charges. Fined
onetime Reagan aide Michael Deaver $100,000 for lying under oath.
Overturned presidential line-item veto legislation.
</P>
<P>
   Hobbies: Sailing on Chesapeake Bay, watching Washington Redskins
games and Shakespeare plays, reading biographies of historical
figures.
</P>
<P>
   Favorite TV shows: NBC's ``Meet the Press'' and ABC's ``This
Week.''
</P>
