agonizing needs and desperation, from girlhood through motherhood
and a parent's death.
</P>
<P>
   THE VERIFICATIONIST. By Donald Antrim. (Knopf, $21.) A slim,
cheerfully cruel novel, set in an all-night pancake house where a
