one Bengali, and their families in a tatty London suburb.
</P>
<P>
   WILD DECEMBERS. By Edna O'Brien. (Houghton Mifflin, $24.) A
lush, poetic novel, set in the remotest imaginable corner of
Ireland, where the most old-fashioned imaginable characters _ a
farmer and his sister _ hide out until overtaken by new machines
and manners from outside. &QL;
</P>
