u l BC-SUMMER-READING-ADVISO     06-07 0272
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUMMER-READING-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A BOOK LOVER'S GUIDE FOR THOSE LAZY, HAZY DAYS OF SUMMER 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GRAB YOUR BEACH BLANKET AND A GOOD BOOK!...
</P>
<P>
   Editors: We are pleased once again to offer you a tempting
8-part list of recommended lawn-chair reading from the
highly-respected New York Times Book Review section. This list has
been selected from books reviewed since the Holiday Books issue of
December 1999. It suggests some of the high points in this year's
fiction, poetry, nonfiction, mysteries and science fiction. The
books are arranged alphabetically under genre headings. For
complete reviews of these books, check out The New York Times' Web
site, www.nytimes.com/books. &QL;
</P>
