<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The toys of summer
 &HT;    By Sabine Morrow
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   School's out for the summer, and kids throughout metro Atlanta
are shucking their book bags and kicking off their shoes. It's time
to feel the power _ the ``power of play'' as the American Toy
Institute calls it.
</P>
<P>
   To help children make the most of their vacation from the
classroom, we found some very cool toys to occupy them during the
long, hot summer.
</P>
<P>
   These playthings should keep idle hands and heads busy for hours
indoors as well as in the great outdoors. We've zeroed in on a few
items that kids can play with solo and others specifically designed
for group activities.
</P>
<P>
   You'll also notice a couple of oldies but goodies jazzed up with
the latest technology, and of course we couldn't leave out toys
that pay homage to the ongoing Pokemon and dinosaur crazes.
</P>
<P>
   So, forget the three R's for a while. Get ready, get set _ and
play!
</P>
<P>
   Pokemon Monopoly
</P>
<P>
   by Parker Brothers
</P>
<P>
   Their parents might have whiled away hours negotiating a deal on
how to acquire precious real estate such as Marvin Gardens and
Boardwalk, but today's kids seem more interested in snagging
Giovanni's Gym and Master Ball. You guessed it, we're talking
Pokemon _ Monopoly, that is. In this version, kids travel from gym
to gym, battling various Pokemon and racking up real estate.
Instead of dollars, players earn Poke Money, and houses and hotels
have been replaced by neon Poke Centers and Poke Marts. And there's
no more arguing who'll get the hat or the iron. Instead, players
will probably fuss over who gets Pikachu.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 8 to adult. About $30. Available at Toys ``R'' Us and
through the Web site at www.toysrus.com.
</P>
<P>
   Hatchling Baby Dinosaur
</P>
<P>
   by Mattel
</P>
<P>
   You can set your calendar by it. Each summer Disney comes up
with a movie event that spawns endless toys, books and trading
cards. Last month, ``Dinosaur'' roared into theaters, and sure
enough, hatchlings are popping out on toy store shelves at record
speed. These soft fabric baby dinos are hatched when you unzip the
plush egg, which emits a soft heartbeat thump. Turn the egg inside
out and a big-eyed baby dinosaur emerges. Press a spot on the
dino's chest and it talks. You can select from the purple Baby
Neera or blue Baby Aladar.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 3 and older. $12.99. Available at Target stores.
</P>
<P>
   Street Glide
</P>
<P>
   by Rand
</P>
<P>
   This zippy little number is sure to start a serious tug of war
between adults and kids. It's a two-wheeled crowd pleaser that can
handle riders weighing up to 175 pounds. And the smooth-rolling
scooter really does glide, thanks to high-performance polyurethane
street wheels. About half as wide as a skateboard and made of
lightweight aluminum, it quickly folds up into an easy-to-tote
bundle. Weighing in at only 7 pounds, the Street Glide offers a
portable little run-around perfect for getting you to your
destination pronto. The Street Glide is not made for stunt riding
or racing and riders must wear a helmet.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 8 and older. About $100. Available at Toys ``R'' Us and
through www.etoys.com.
</P>
<P>
   Jump Rope Rock by Oddzon
</P>
<P>
   Skip to the music with this jump rope that features seven
electronic songs. You control tempo and add sound effects by
pressing buttons on the plastic handles. The music automatically
shuts off when you stop jumping.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 6 and up. About $10. Available at Toys ``R'' Us and
through www.etoys.com.
</P>
<P>
   Blue's Clues
</P>
<P>
   Spin &AMP; Splash
</P>
<P>
   by Fisher-Price
</P>
<P>
   Dogs and children playing in the water is a typical summer
scene. Now your kids can splash courtesy of that wacky pooch Blue.
Just hook her up to a garden hose and her ears will spin and spray
water. Flowers sprout from her bucket and water squirts from her
watering pail. Blue provides an ideal way to cool off on a hot
summer's afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 18 months and up. About $19.99. Available at Toys ``R''
Us and through www.etoys.com.
</P>
<P>
   Firefly Lantern by Coleman
</P>
<P>
   Whether you take the kids camping in the mountains or in the
great outdoors of your back yard, consider the new Firefly Lantern.
Capturing and keeping those elusive fireflies is always a
challenge, but Coleman's lightweight lantern provides a roomy
sanctuary for the flashing critters. Made of plastic with a
screened middle and swivel top, the lantern's light comes from the
fireflies _ no batteries or fuel needed. And no more punching holes
in a jar lid!
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 6 and up. $9.99. Available through www.etoys.com.
</P>
<P>
   Tie Dye Kit by Creativity for Kids
</P>
<P>
   Yes, tie dye is back and everything you need to create
individual, colorful designs is included in this tie dye kit. Make
your own rainbow-colored swirls and splashes by wrapping and
knotting fabric with special cords that contain dyes in six colors.
Think beyond wildly colored T-shirts and jeans with this kit
because it also contains items to make a heart-shaped pillow and a
stuffed teddy bear.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 7 and up. $14.99. Available at Zany Brainy stores.
</P>
<P>
   Wave Hoop by Maui Toys
</P>
<P>
   OK, other than the fact that it comes in glittery, neon colors,
this longtime favorite looks pretty much like the original Wham-O
Hula Hoop we remember from childhood. However, the folks at Maui
Toys want you to know that their version practically ``hoops by
itself.'' Therein lies the difference. The wave in the name refers
to liquid inside the hoop along with a flow-through plug that keeps
the hoop suspended in midair. This toy has hit a variety of ``top
toys'' lists since it was introduced earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 3 and up. $5.99. Available at Toys ``R'' Us.
</P>
<P>
   JamCam, Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Digital Camera by KB Gear
</P>
<P>
   Kids love to take pictures, but raising a budding Ansel Adams
can get costly when you consider how much film those pint-size
photographers can gobble up. And often the resulting photos consist
of little more than Rover's nose, half a shoe and plenty of grass.
However, with JamCam, Jr. you don't have to worry about film or
developing costs. This sturdy, easy to use digital camera is
designed especially for little hands and curious minds. No film
needed, just snap, then download the pictures into your home
computer and you easily can nix the mistakes.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 8 and up. $69.99. Available at Zany Brainy stores and
through www.etoys.com.
</P>
<P>
   Matchbox Car Wash by Mattel
</P>
<P>
   To keep your cars looking their best, consider the Matchbox Car
Wash where you can wash, rinse and dry your Matchbox and Hot Wheels
vehicles. You might want to wash those dirty trucks and cars
outside since this toy uses soap and water. The car wash comes with
a Volkswagen ready to cruise through the swinging gates for a buggy
bath. Some adult assembly is required.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ages 3 and up. $17.99. Available at Toys ``R'' Us and through
www.toysrus.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
