<P>
   MICROSOFT RULING
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ U.S. District Judge Thomas Penfield
Jackson issues a ruling in the Microsoft antitrust case that is
expected to break the software giant into two parts. Details of the
historic ruling, its significance, and what's next in the legal
process. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-REACT _ WASHINGTON _ Legal and business reaction to
the Microsoft ruling. (Geewax, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-JUDGE _ WASHINGTON _ Consider the various public faces
of Thomas Penfield Jackson, the burly U.S. District Court judge who
on Wednesday threw the book at Microsoft for having flouted the
nation's antitrust laws. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   JUDGE-BIOBOX _ Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson at a glance. (Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-GLANCE _ WASHINGTON _ Highlights of the Micosoft
ruling. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-HARDWARE _ Almost since the existence of the personal
computer, PC makers have been inextricably tied to Microsoft and
Windows. But if Microsoft is broken into pieces, it could
significantly change what PC makers put on their machines. (Pletz,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-SOFTWARE _ Pick up any piece of software these days
and it's nearly a given that it will be written for either a
Windows or Mac format. But what happens when Windows becomes a new
company, with new chiefs and a new agenda? We chat with software
makers about what a breakup of Microsoft might mean. (Cocks, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-INVESTORS _ When word came down weeks ago that
Microsoft would likely be split apart, investors and Wall Street
analysts cheered the move. Why? In other big anti-trust breakups -
AT&AMP;T, Standard Oil, etc - the stock price of the successor
companies have always been worth more than the original company.
(Schatz, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WITH list of biggest MSFT holders.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-PARTNERS _ We talk to local companies who have either
partnered with MSoft as equity partners or marketing partners about
whether they're confused about what will happen to those
agreements. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-GATES _ A short on how much Bill Gates' personal net
worth has been affected by the case. (Luke, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINES _ Following reports of a meeting of second-tier
American and Delta executives in which the notion of a merger
between the two _ considered highly unlikely _ was discussed along
with other consolidation scenarios. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   SOFTWARE _ WASHINGTON _ The Business Software Alliance, a trade
group holding its annual CEOs convention, will release the results
of a survey about the future of the software industry. (Glass, Cox
News Service). 20.
</P>
