<P>
   SUNDAY, June 25
</P>
<P>
   BRITIAIN-CRIME-$ADV25 _ LONDON _ The crime rate has risen
dramatically in Britain, now
</P>
<P>
   exceeding the crime rate in the United States. London has a
worse crime rate than New York City. This is causing considerable
concern here in the land of gunless coppers. (Roughton).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PRISONERS-$ADV25 _ MITROVICA, Kosovo _ There are
reportedly more than 1,500 Kosovar Albanians still held in Serb
prisons without being charged. Many of them were rounded up by Serb
paramilitaries during last spring's ethnic cleansing campaign.
Serbs call them prisoners of war, but their wives and mothers call
them hostages. The United Nations can do little to secure their
release _ another criticism people have about the U.N. It's a very
politically touchy subject. The cease-fire accords left out any
mention of prisoner releases, for a number of reasons. But now,
families are left with no recourse except to pay bribes and ransoms
to get their relatives out of jail, paying anywhere from $4,000 to
$10,000. We tag along and bear witness to one of these exchanges at
the Kosovo-Serbia border to tell the story of these families being
reunited. (Coker).
</P>
<P>
   With Photos.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-PRI-$ADV25 _ MEXICO CITY _ The presidential election on
July 2 has political observers and experts asking a rather unusual
question: What if the Instituational Revolutionary Party, the PRI,
doesn't retain presidential power after 71 years? If opposition
candidate Vicente Fox is able to topple PRI candidate Francisco
Labastida Ochoa, what happens to seven-decades of social
infrastructure? Is there a worst-case scenario? (Ferriss).
</P>
<P>
   With US-MEXICO-$ADV25 _ WASHINGTON _ What's the U.S. view of the
Mexican election, and is there a lot at stake? Would a Fox win
change trade relations at all? What about the war on
</P>
<P>
   drugs? The likely answer is very little change at all. (Deans).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move in both International and Commentary
categories.
</P>
<P>
   GUN-LICENSING _ WASHINGTON _ One of the goals of the Million Mom
March is widely seen as unattainable _ licensing gun owners much as
we do drivers and hair stylists. A look at why some people see
licensing as a key to reducing gun violence, and others as a danger
to liberty. (Moscoso).
</P>
