<P>
   EISNER-PIRACY (Washington) _ At a press conference on Wednesday,
Disney Co. chief Michael Eisner called for new anti-piracy measures
and reiterated the entertainment industry's concerns about
copyright infringement. His appearance in the nation's capital is
part of a congressional technology summit and lobbying by the
Motion Picture Association of America. By Bill Hillburg. (Will move
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   HOLLYWOOD-AUCTION (Los Angeles) _ Ben Hur's baton is up for
sale. So is Maxwell Smart's umbrella phone. A five day auction by
Ellis Props of Hollywood begins Thursday. The items represent the
entire contents of Ellis, with some dating back to the 1800s. Those
who can't make it in person can also bid online. By Orith Goldberg.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   STRAWBERRY-SEASON (Ventura, Calif.) _ For Ventura County
strawberry growers, this year's season has been the worst they've
seen in decades because of a glut of berries on the market and bad
weather in early spring. While it looks like it's going to be a
record year for the rest of California, with 20 percent more fruit
picked than last year, numbers in Ventura County are lower than
usual. By Jennifer Klein. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California state news files.)
</P>
