<P>
   KLM-BRITISH-AIR (Undated) _ The game of musical chairs that is
sweeping the global airline industry expanded to yet more players
Wednesday but it appears that it will still be some time before the
music stops. In London, British Airways PLC, Europe's largest
airline, and the Netherlands-based carrier, KLM Royal Dutch NV,
announced that they had entered into merger negotiations following
weeks of rumors. Meanwhile, across the Atlantic, AMR Corp., the
parent of American Airlines, and Delta Airlines held preliminary
merger discussions earlier this week, according to two people
familiar with the talks. By Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
