<P>
   From Billboard issue of June 17
</P>
<P>
   WEBPHILE
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tonight: The 2000 Toyota Comedy Festival is happening in New
York City through Saturday and among the festivities is a panel
discussion with the editors and writers of the Onion, the
gut-busting satiric newspaper and Web site (www.theonion.com). The
event, dubbed ``The State of the Onion,'' will be moderated by
CNN's Jeff Greenfield. The video webcast begins at 8 tonight. ...
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Sunday: ``Return of the Rock'' is a new compilation from MTV
and Roadrunner Records that gathers some of the hottest bands in
hard rock. Sonicnet.com (www.sonicnet.com) offers a chat with two
of the bands represented on the CD, Incubus and Coal Chamber, at 8
p.m. Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Monday: Actor Christian Bale interacts with fans on Yahoo!
Chat (chat.yahoo.com) at 4 p.m. He'll talk about his role in the
upcoming remake of ``Shaft.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Wednesday: R&AMP;B quartet Destiny's Child will interact with fans
in an online chat at 9 p.m on twec.com (www.twec.com). ... Sizzling
British dance music duo Groove Armada is catching American ears
with the track ``I See You Baby.'' The duo's U.S. tour won't be
stopping in Atlanta, so you might want to catch a live webcast from
the House of Blues in Chicago at 10 p.m. (www.hob.com).
</P>
<P>
   _Shane Harrison writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
