<P>
   BUSH-INTERVIEW (Austin, Texas) _ George W. Bush says he is
narrowing his list of prospective vice presidential running mates
on the Republican ticket, with an eye on candidates who would be
loyal and capable of serving as president. The presumptive
Republican presidential nominee tells editors and executives of the
Hearst Newspapers that he expects to reach a decision in coming
weeks but will most likely delay his announcement until closer to
the Republican convention in Philadelphia that begins on July 31.
By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
