<SLUG> BC-FILM-JOURNEYOFMAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THEY FLY THROUGH THE AIR IN 3-D
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TODD CAMP 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The world of Cirque du Soleil is so immense that it takes a 3-D
IMAX movie to capture the magic at its best.
</P>
<P>
   The French-Canadian art circus made up of dozens of companies
performing in shows around the world has yet to find its place
within the celluloid realm. Performance recordings pale in
comparison to the live experience, and the troupe's one narrative
foray, last year's ``Alegria,'' proved that style can't always
overcome a shortage of substance.
</P>
<P>
   Fortunately, the three-dimensional, larger-than-life IMAX film
format solves the feeling of disconnection while a simple
morality-based story line _ stay in touch with the child within, a
common Cirque theme _ told with pantomime and narration (by the
great Ian McKellen) prevents the possibility of flimsy
characterization spoiling the mix.
</P>
<P>
   The result is a terrific introduction for anyone unfamiliar with
Cirque, and a delightful adventure for its die-hard fans. Made up
of recognizable pieces from almost every Cirque period, ``Journey''
begins in an undersea world of colorful swimmers performing in
perfect harmony and then travels to multiple landscapes signifying
the various stages of life.
</P>
<P>
   Bungee jumpers bounce in a lush forest, a dancer spins a giant
metallic cube atop a rocky desert plain and nimble acrobats perform
seemingly impossible airborne routines over the marble floor of an
ornate hall.
</P>
<P>
   The film strikes a nice balance with its 3-D, avoiding the usual
in-your-face gimmicks while still offering dazzling visuals. But
it's the patented Cirque blend of beautiful costumes, amazing
artistry and acrobatic prowess, all to the dreamy, addictive
melodies of composer Benoit Jutras, that elevates ``Journey'' into
a dizzying, often emotional experience.
</P>
<P>
   After the shameless commercialism of ``Siegfried &AMP; Roy: The
Magic Box,'' it's good to know that Cirque's permanent shows on the
Vegas strip haven't corrupted the troupe enough to trade artistic
integrity for crass spectacle. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Film: ``Journey of Man'' &QL; 
Running time: 38 minutes &QL; 
Rating: PG &QL; 
Score: 4 on a 1-5 scale &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
</P>
</TEXT>
