<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JUNE 8
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-WORLD-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 6,
about the retirement of Alija Izetbegovic next October misstated
his position. He is one of the three presidents of Bosnia and
Herzegovina, not president of the country's Muslim-Croatian
component, the Bosnian Federation.
</P>
<P>
   BC-REFORM-PARTY-NYT (moved on Monday, June 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 5,
about Ross Perot's inclination against running for the Reform Party
nomination for president referred inaccurately to party officials'
approach to Patrick J. Buchanan. Senior party officials have said
that associates of Perot let Buchanan know he was welcome to seek
the nomination. Russell J. Verney, an associate of Perot, did not
say that Perot invited Buchanan to run.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NJ-ELECT-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 6,
about the primary in New Jersey referred incorrectly to the rarity
of a United States Senate race there without an incumbent. Bill
Bradley chose not to seek re-election in 1996; Senator Frank R.
Lautenberg's decision last year to step down at the end of his term
was not the first such move in 18 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
